op align=left class=m><span class=title> DarkElf Hide Skill</span><hr size=1> I like this skill a lot, it's one of my hotkeys. Someone said it only works for level 1-2 mobs, which do go indifferent when I stop and click it, but not the higher level ones.  While in loio, all but the undead would go indifferent if I waited about 5 seconds before clicking it. Or by the time you click it twice and wait for the button to pop again.  So.. is this a latency reason why I have to wait in a single spot with no movement before preparing to hide? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=milaru>Milaru</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Don't mind me,<BR>it's the PMS talking!</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/1/02 6:47:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18137.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DarkElf Hide Skill</span><hr size=1> it's set at 50, sometimes you fail, sometimes you don't. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eaminwhitefalcon>Eamin Whitefalcon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>¡Viva la inquisición!</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/1/02 6:49:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18137.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://chuma.cas.usf.edu/~dking3/Eamin_small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DarkElf Hide Skill</span><hr size=1> The vast majority of the time you fail, and because you're not a Rogue, you can't tell.<br>
<br>
Your best bet is to sit down, target a mob that's below or above indifferently, and just keep trying. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uelpiper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elpiper</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/1/02 6:59:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18137.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.pizzaladifference.com/Stitchanim.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DarkElf Hide Skill</span><hr size=1> As explained above, target a KOS mob before you attempt to Hide.  After you click your hide button, /con the mob and see if you're now indifferent.  If not, click and try again.<br>
<br>
Another option is if you are with a partner.  I played a lot with my wood elf Druid girlfriend, and we'd sit facing each other and try to hide to med.  If you disappear from your partner's screen, you're hiding successfully.<br>
<br>
This skill was of GREAT use to me, to safely med in places like Skyfire.  You just have to be careful there are no see invis mobs around, such as undead or caster mobs. <p><br><br><p><html><p align="center"><embed

